</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,971,1374]" box="[151,1436,1000,1022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1000,1022]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">- Forewing without spot inside antemedial line............................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,971,1374]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
2. Male flagella with pectination on basal 2/3 of ventral side, costa with a small thorn distally (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1160,1029,1051]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–5" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[173,1403,210,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-27@4.[151,1435,181,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–5. Merulempista pectinata sp. nov. 4, Adult, paratype, female; 5, Male genitalia, phallus, and 8th abdominal segment, holotype, slide no. LHX13258. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6621360/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), posterior margin of antrum serrated in female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[500,557,1059,1081]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–7" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[250,1336,203,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[227,1360,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 6–7. Female genitalia of Merulempista species. 6, M. similirubriptera sp. nov., paratype, slide no. LHX13254; 7, M. pectinata sp. nov., paratype, slide no. LHX11128. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6621364" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6621364/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
)....................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Zhang &amp; Li, 2022" authorityName="Liu &amp; Zhang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[1232,1353,1059,1080]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Merulempista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1232,1353,1059,1080]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">M. pectinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1360,1436,1059,1080]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1436,1059,1080]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,971,1374]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
- Male flagellae without pectination, costa without thorn, posterior margin of antrum smooth in female genitalia (
<bibRefCitation author="Ren, Y. D. &amp; Liu, S. R. &amp; Li, H. H." pageId="1" pageNumber="294" pagination="65 - 75" refId="ref4961" refString="Ren, Y. D., Liu, S. R. &amp; Li, H. H. (2011) Review of the genus Merulempista Roesler, 1967 (Lepidoptera, Pyralidae) from China, with description of two new species. ZooKeys, 77, 65 - 75. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 77.938" type="journal article" year="2011">Ren and Li, 2011</bibRefCitation>
)................................................................................. 
