</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,971,1374]" box="[151,1436,1176,1198]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1176,1198]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">- Distal part of process in costa pointed..................................................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,971,1374]" box="[151,1436,1205,1227]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1205,1227]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
4. Costal process triangular, cornuti not reach end of phallus........................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li and Ren" authorityYear="2011" box="[1304,1436,1205,1227]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Merulempista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubriptera">
<emphasis box="[1304,1436,1205,1227]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">M. rubriptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,971,1374]" box="[151,1436,1235,1257]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1235,1257]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">- Costal process digitiform, cornuti reach end of phallus....................................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
